review_text: I tried these once from the store, and when they stopped carrying them I had to track them down! I have been ordering them ever since! I love these gummies, I only have one big problem - the packaging is deceptive. It's labeled 5mg gummies, but if you look at the serving size it says that two gummies have 5 mg of melatonin. So each gummy is only packing about 2.5 mg of melatonin. Not a big deal, but problematic because I wanted a higher dose of melatonin so I'd have to take fewer gummies at a time. Aside from the deceptive label, the gummies are delicious and effective. Seriously, if they made these as candy without the melatonin I would be downing them! The berry flavor is delicious, and the consistency is very soft when freshly opened. Toward the bottom of the bottle they get a little stiffer from air exposure, but still very good. I usually take two gummies (5mg) at night to encourage faster sleep (otherwise it can take me 45-90 minutes to fall asleep), and three (7.5mg) if it's really important I get a restful night sleep. I wouldn't say they're really fast acting, but they definitely make a difference. Usually within 15 minutes I can feel a wave of sleepiness.

review_text: Really helped with my insomnia and it has a great taste! I would take 2 per night and try to wean off on taking these to avoid dependence. Be careful when you take melatonin, as there is not enough research on exogenous melatonin use and how it affects your pineal gland's natural production of melatonin. I started feeling dependent on it and stopped using it completely, but it's a great tool for sleep aid. review_text: My son (Almost 6) has always been a night owl. I’ve tried many different children’s melatonin from Amazon/in stores and could never find one that worked well for us. I knew school would be starting soon and really needed to get his bedtime routine set so that he had enough sleep for a full day of kindergarten. These have worked great for us. They’re not coated in a bunch of sugar and my son says the flavor is good. I’ve tried it myself it is peachy, but not too sweet and there’s definitely a slight herbal taste to it but not strong. Texture is like a soft/springy gummy bear. After trying it myself it gave me a sense of calmness and basically lulls me to sleep. I think the slightly higher dosage of melatonin .5mg more than the usual 1mg and the herbal blend make a huge difference. Most of the children’s melatonin we’ve tried has always had 1mg or less and no herbs. The key is to keep a bedtime routine in combination with the melatonin. I give it to my son about 30 min to an hour before bedtime after a bath then it’s brush teeth, pajamas, lights down, and quiet time in bed. Always within 30 min to an hour and a half at most he’s sleeping. I plan to eventually have him off of the melatonin, but for now it works for us because I would rather him settle into a routine and be well rested vs. not have enough sleep and fight to be awake. I am grateful for these as it has been a great help with getting my son’s sleep routine in order before school started and in general.

Based on my experience and the false labeling I would wager there's nothing in these. I don't care about getting a refund, I want 3rd party validated tests on this product. As well as some response from Amazon regarding what is obviously false marketing. Just as a reference point, I've used at least 20+ different brands of Melatonin at this point. I've used it for over 7 years now every night. I know when something is and isn't working. I work in the natural health industry myself and use a wide variety of supplements as well! I decided to try this out based on the reviews. Sugar free Gummies sound like a yummy way to consume Melatonin right? All I can say is after my experience, these reviews MUST be FAKE or there's a placebo effect going on here. Besides my experience which I'll explain below. I have a hard time understanding how there are 12.5 GRAMS worth of herbs packed into a 2 gummy serving x 50 servings = 625 GRAMS of herbal powder, lets not include the weight of the gummies themselves. That means a bottle weighs over a pound BEFORE you add in the weight of the gelatin and sweetener? So the total weight is what a kg? I couldn't find the weight of the bottle anywhere and I had already eaten a majority of them before I thought to weigh it (I snack on them, they are tasty! I'm chewing on one as I write this very sentence and I don't plan to sleep for another 7 hours). The bottle could not have weighed more than 350 grams though, probably closer to 250-300 grams. None of this makes sense. HERBAL WEIGHT BREAKDOWN: Just to clarify 4.25 GRAMS of passion flower is a bit heavier than taking 8 x 500mg capsules! Chamomile same story, almost as much claimed for lemon balm. Ok so lets just round that out. We're looking at around 24 x 500mg CAPSULES worth of powder crammed into TWO TINY GUMMIES!!! This is just a flat out lie! How are these guys in business? For them to come around and say whoops, just add a mg on there, it's just a typo, our mistake would NOT be acceptable. People buy this thinking there's an absurd amount of herbs crammed in here, besides a lot of melatonin which I'm convinced is ALSO not present. --- My Experience DAY 1: First night I tried it, was the first time I've had difficulty sleeping in a while. I took another melatonin I had on hand and in 15 min I was out. DAY 2: Tried it again, again nothing. I had my GF try it as well that night. Also nada. We both tried one of my other melatonin's on hand and we were both out like a light. DAY 3: Tried again. Same story, this time I decided to take them 2 HOURS BEFORE BED as well I made sure to chew them slowly and hold in my mouth for at least ten minutes before swallowing. I didn't feel even slightly fatigued. I waited until an hour in bed to take something else to help me sleep. DAY 4: I tried taking them before a nap, didn't help at all. I tried taking them that night again several hours before bed and again at bed. I took about 10 that night. No effect whatsoever! DAY 5: I now just chew them in the evening but now knowing there's zero effect I make sure I take another melatonin supplement so I actually fall asleep. My GF and I now eat them as a snack throughout the day, it's THAT ineffective. I'm convinced there's nothing in these. I would go so far to say that someone needs to test and verify this stuff. The label is incorrect in terms of amounts. The weight listed on the SUPPLEMENT FACTS panel is heavier than the actual bottle, I'm only talking about the herbs it contains! To the owners, the lack of attention to your label already speaks volumes. You can't tell me that both my GF and I can take 3mg of a normal melatonin and feel sleepy in 30 minutes, but can take 10 of your gummies, which should be 50mg of melatonin and still FEEL NOTHING!
review_header: FALSE LABELLING! Also Not Effective AT ALL! BUYER BEWARE!

review_text: Amazon is the most annoying place to buy supplements. The dosage, price-per-mg, added ingredients, certifications, etc., are incredibly hard to track down. Sigh. review_text: I wasn’t getting a deep sleep for a while. It might have been due to stress or maybe it was too hot in my sleep quarters or something else but I just knew when I woke up, I felt groggy. reviewed_product_attribute: Size: 140 Count (Pack of 1) | Style: Regular Strength
review_text: I bought these Gummies using Prime and had them delivered using 2-Day Shipping. The Gummies arrived in perfect condition, and were not melted at all. The Gummies left a waxy residue on the inside of the bottle, but this has no affected the Gummies themselves. Taste-wise, these Gummies have a peach-like flavour. They are similar in taste to the peach Vitafusion Multivites Gummies. Personally, I'm a fan! I am taking Melatonin as I suffer from Delayed Sleep Phase Syndrome (DSPS) and I naturally fall asleep around 3am and wake up by 12pm. I am trying to shift my circadian rhythm so that I fall asleep by 12am. As this was my first experience with Melatonin, I ate a single Gummy (1.5mg Melatonin) before bedtime (10pm). This made me sleepy within 15 minutes of taking it. This sleepiness did not feel natural, it was more of a drugged feeling, and my mind and body felt sluggish. I fell asleep and awoke the next day at 1.30pm, still feeling drugged (the Melatonin 'hangover'). This meant 1.5mg was too high of a dose and I needed to reduce the amount. The next night, I cut a single Gummy (~0.4mg) into quarters, and ate 1 of those quarters before bedtime. I began feeling sleepy 15-20 minutes later, and went to bed. However, my brain did not go into sleep-mode, and I was conscious of being sleepy but unable to fall asleep. I also woke up frequently throughout the night and had trouble going back to sleep. I will continue experimenting with this until I figure out the Goldilocks amount of Melatonin that I need, or until I give up. My process is to take half of a Gummy (~0.7mg) next, and either increase or reduce the amount by 1/8. If this does not work, I may switch to the extended release 300mcg tablets, or the liquid Melatonin (0.25mg per drop). If you suffer from DSPS like I do, then taking a higher dosage of Melatonin will likely not have the desired effect we need to shift the circadian rhythm. In fact, the body may become unresponsive to the higher dosage or Melatonin, so that it will no longer have any effect. Research tends to suggest that DSPS sufferers benefit from very low doses of extended-release Melatonin (between 0.3mg and 1 mg), meaning that 1.5mg, 3mg, 2.5mg, and 5mg are all possibly far too high for us. However, even though we are trying to alert the body that it is time to sleep using Melatonin, the body itself may reject it as according to its circadian rhythm (and the time the body begins releasing its own Melatonin), it is not time to sleep as yet. In such cases, the external Melatonin may not have any effect. The main points to come away with are: Melatonin may work for DSPS sufferers, or it may not. It depends on how the body reacts to it. Melatonin should not be taken as a 'sleeping pill', as it is a hormone that regulates your circadian rhythm. If your circadian rhythm is fine and in sync with society's norms (i.e. you fall asleep at a 'normal' hour and wake up at a 'normal' hour in time for a 9-5 job), then you should NOT take Melatonin. Even though these Gummies are delicious, you should only give them to children under medical supervision, as it is a HORMONE and can have an impact on puberty. People have reportedly felt depressed while taking Melatonin, so use your discretion. If you realize your mood is being altered, stop taking Melatonin and speak to a medical practitioner. If you feel drugged or lethargic, reduce the amount of Melatonin that you are taking. There are more side effects that you may experience while taking Melatonin, so please take some time to read these before taking this Gummy. I will continue to update this review from time to time to share my ongoing experiences with these Melatonin Gummies in hopes that it will help other DSPS sufferers out there. Update: February 14th, 2019. A little over 1 year later. These gummies are effective for me, in terms of making me sleepy. Initially, I only needed a small amount, but then I needed 1 whole gummy, then a bit more than 1 whole gummy, and now I'm onto needing two whole gummies. I'm very sad to say that the melatonin did not actually work in terms of helping me adjust my circadian rhythm. Instead, they do act like a sleeping aid, where they make me drowsy, and I would have a very restful, undisturbed, almost drugged sleep. Even people being noisy didn't wake me up. I don't feel drugged when I wake up though, I feel very refreshed. I've now stopped using these unless I need to wake up early. At this point I'm using it like a sleeping aid, which wasn't what I had initially planned. I sincerely hope it helps you in regulating your circadian rhythm. It just doesn't seem like it'll work out that way for me.
review_header: The Gummies arrived in perfect condition, and were not melted at all

review_text: I bought this product to help me fall asleep. It DID do that. However, within two days of starting it, I woke up with excruciating back pain in my mid back. It hurt to breathe. I am not a person who suffers from back pain or problems and wondered what in the world I had done to hurt myself. Each night I would take the melatonin gummies and each morning I would wake with back pain. Two days after the back pain began I sneezed and my nose began bleeding. It bled so much my hands were full of blood by the time I realized what was happening and ran to the bathroom. My nose continued to bleed for almost 10 minutes. I also dont suffer from nosebleeds or have a clotting problem. After almost six days of agony in my back and a bloody nose, I thought back on what was different and realized the ONLY thing different was I had been taking those melatonin gummies. However, I couldnt believe a harmless sleep aid could do this to me. To test my theory I didnt take the gummies one night. The next morning I awoke with zero back pain. I felt great. That night I took the gummies again and the next morning I woke with excruciating back pain. (See the pattern here!) Again, I also experienced a traumatic nosebleed. Neither of these things are listed in potential side effects. However, the 1% contraindications do list pain and nosebleeds. I guess I'm in the 1%, but I bet I'm not the only one. If you began experiencing back pain after taking these, stop like I did and see if your pain goes away. While these may be helpful for bringing on sleep, the debilitating back pain is not worth it. I hope this helps someone.

review_text: I read a review on here where someone was saying if you don’t take more than you should, it won’t cause weird dreams. Not true, in my experience. The melatonin gummies I’ve been purchasing, they have been 2.5mg melatonin per gummy, or 5mg per 2-gummy serving. I’ve been trying several brands, but they’ve all been the same dosage. I usually take 2.5mg (one gummy) just if I need help falling asleep, or 5mg (2 gummies) if I want to make sure I stay asleep through the night. I’ve been using them a lot more, more recently, so I was looking for a higher dosage option so I wouldn’t run out as fast each time. Thinking I was making a smart decision, I ordered these max strength ones. I don’t need the full 2-gummy 10mg dose of this, but I could take 1/2 gummy if I needed my 2.5mg to fall asleep, or 1 gummy if 5mg to stay asleep - same dosage as I’ve been doing. I have yet to have more than 1/2 of one yet (2.5 mg). I have tried this four times, and have had four crazy dreams. I rarely remember dreams so I can’t say for sure, but I have no memory of crazy dreams with any other melatonin, even if I’ve take 5mg of it. But, I very vividly remember the four dreams I’ve had while using this. I will use this when needed until my next Amazon haul when I order something else, but i sincerely doubt I can make it through this bottle!

reviewed_product_attribute: Size: 50 Count (Pack of 1) | Style: Kids
review_text: My poor son hates bedtime more than anything else in the world. For the 8 and a half years of his life, bedtime has been an hour or more of tears, frustration, me lying down in bed with him, every relaxation technique known to man, bribes, punishments, bedtime stories, mattress pads, different pajamas... I swear to you, I was at my wits' end, and so was he. He was crying on my shoulder at midnight two months ago, "Why can't I just sleep? How do you do it?" And I just... I couldn't help him. He has ADHD, and part of it for him is he just can't turn his brain off. His dad's ex-wife and I were chatting, and she told me she gives her daughter Melatonin gummies. I was disbelieving; Melatonin doesn't work for me, why would they work for him? But she encouraged me to give them a try, so I ordered these. People, this changed my life. I swear to you. They changed my son's life. I'm leaving this review now because I'm on the product page buying another bottle of them. I don't ever want to go back to bedtime without gummies. 15 minutes. That's all it takes. We still have to have some routine and put on bedtime music for him to fall asleep to, they're not a sedative, he still has to relax in bed. But before, he would relax in bed for an hour and a half. Now, it's literally 15 minutes. I almost cried the first night. I was skeptical- would these work? Would they keep working night after night? Yes. Yes yes yes yes yes. He's finally SLEEPING. The gummies themselves: they're soft and easy to chew. My son is very picky, and didn't love the flavor at first, but it's grown on him. He gives the flavor 4 out of 5. It doesn't seem to matter if he takes these on an empty stomach. And I give them some lead time to start working before bed, but it doesn't seem to matter if he takes one an hour before bed or 30 min before. There have been times we've gotten home late from visiting relatives, and had to give him his gummy and stick him straight in bed, and it's hard to tell at that point whether the gummy still works exactly the same or if he's tired from having a big day, but he's still out in about 20 minutes. Our routine now is that 30 minutes before lights out, he takes a gummy and brushes his teeth. Then he lies down, he gets to watch one episode of a show, then we change the TV to a nature documentary (always the same one) to give his ADHD brain something to focus on, and he's out in 15 minutes. Sometimes less. This is insane. I'm not 100% sure it's not magic. You have no idea the relief of, after almost nine years of this child not sleeping, of bedtime being the worst battleground in our lives, of tears and frustration and trying every single thing we could possibly think of... finally... sleep. He just... sleeps. My baby is even happier than I am. He doesn't have to stress about it anymore; sleep just comes naturally like it's supposed to. I can't promise these will work for your kids. But I can tell you they're absolutely worth a try; they changed our lives.

review_text: This is a review of the Vitafusion Extra Strength Melatonin Blackberry 5mg 120 count Gummies. Summary – I have a terrible time getting my mind to shut off at the end of the day to get a good nights rest. I have mainly been using Tylenol PM and diphenhydramine. Tylenol PM does typically work but sometimes it will not for some reason. Since it has acetaminophen, I do not like to use it much. My main sleep aid was diphenhydramine. This causes dry mouth and I found for some reason it prevents me from sleeping if I am not able to get to sleep within the first hour. When I read about this, I was skeptical but thought it would be worth looking into. I have been using these for over a month now and could not be happier. Unlike most sleeping pills which can cause dry mouth or leave you feeling terrible the next morning, these have no apparent side effect so far. It is hard to explain how these work. They do not make me tired yet when I am ready to go to sleep, I can do so very quickly now without any early waking up. When I wake up, I am not groggy. Each of the gummies is 5mg and the bottle has 120 gummies. The blackberry is what we have and the flavor is very nice. Did not get to try on a flight yet, however, these are supposed to help with jet lag. While not a factor for me, these are also gluten free. Note – One serving size is 2 gummies which give you 5mg. If you take four gummies, you are getting 10mg. Calories per serving is 15 and this bottle will give you 60 servings. Note – I am certainly not a doctor and if in doubt or unclear of all side effects-dosage or other issues, you should consult a doctor before using. Hope this helps and as with all my reviews, I will update this should something change.

review_text: I'm an insomniac. I have it bad. So bad in fact that the docs have had me on Ambien since 1997. I literally couldn't sleep without it. I tried to wean myself off many times only to lie awake for days until I would nearly go mad. I began to talk with my cardiologist who pleaded with me to come off the sleeping pills to which I replied I would happily do so if he could tell me how on earth to sleep without them. When he suggested melatonin I laughed at him. I never in a million years thought a natural supplement could ever help me. But it was worth a try! I researched and read reviews until I settled on this brand. I picked the extra strength for obvious reasons. First night I tried 2. Nothing. Second night I ate 4. Still nothing. 3rd night I ate 6 and FINALLY for the first time in OVER TWENTY YEARS I fell asleep without Ambien! When I woke up the next day I absolutely couldn't believe it. Yes, 6 is a lot, but considering that it used to take a lot of big pharma to knock me out, I don't mind! I won't lie and say I don't still need Ambien from time to time but I'm only needing it maybe once or twice a week now. And even after some months have gone by, my melatonin tolerance hasn't waivered. I figured by now I'd be eating jars of this stuff every night, but for me 6 is the magic number! As long as they keep making this I'll definitely keep buying it!!!

Something is off in how they're packaged, because they are totally fresh, not stale at all, and I store them in the jar with the lid properly screwed on, well within the temperature range Google says is correct (the bottle doesn't say anything about it). If the only issue was separating them I wouldn't bother to complain, but the opening is so small you can't get any out once they're stuck, and they're so gummy that trying to break them up with a chopstick or something doesn't work at all. It just sticks in them. Annoying enough that I won't rebuy them even though otherwise they were great. Boo.
review_header: Stuck together into a giant lump even though they're fresh and properly stored.
